### Step 2: Refactor Unnecessary event_queue Backlog Queries (Optional Optimization)
The health check endpoint `system_health` does:
```javascript
const pendingSnapshot = await db.collection("event_queue").where("status", "==", "pending").get();
const backlogSize = pendingSnapshot.size;
```
To be absolutely safe and avoid any potential runtime failures or performance overhead on `event_queue` queries, we will refactor `system_health` to use the pre-aggregated `queue_backlog_size` from `system_metrics` realtime document, matching the preferred pattern of not querying `event_queue` again when the data exists elsewhere.

